    <item>
      <title>My take on needed pvp tweaks</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=12855#M12855</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Alright, so i'm posting this right before the servers come up and we are able to see what changes come to pvp with tss, but under the assumption that some fundamental problems in pvp will remain the same, i'm making this post. Hopefully we can get some good feedback on this thread, since we know soe only changes things when&amp;nbsp;a large group of people agree on it.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Bard: Everyone hates bards, theres nothing more annoying then not being able to kill someone because they run to fast. Coupled with our dispell/mez/manadrain, bards are very annoying to encounter in pvp. But then again, so are enchanters. So are clerics, so are alot of classes. Bards/encs/clerics are all annoying pvp because they do things you don't want them to, pell your buffs, take your mana, or keep the person you want to kill from dying. This happens so often that some people have actually suggested that heals should be nerfed in pvp. I'm not one of them, but it just goes to show what can come from people being annoyed. That being said, should bards really be nerfed based on their ability to annoy you, or their ability to actually kill you? I've always been a believer of the later. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Zerker snare for example was nerfed because it landed every time, and increased your chance of death about 90% when facing a group. Now thats a needed nerf. Monk 2.0 and t-staff was nerfed because they immobolized a victim for 10 secs at a time per proc, and the monk would often get frequent procs in a row. That also is a needed nerf in my point of view. Bards have never been to good at killing though. Not since increasing resists have made our dots useless, our only form of damage is melee. And when you have a 300 dps class vs a 500 dps hybrid or 600-700 dps pure melee, its easy to guess what happens most of the time. Not to say that bards desparetly need pvp help, a bard with enough aa and gear can melee effectively if they use the proper tactics, just never as good as other melee classes with their same level of gear/aa. So bards are rarely a threat when it comes to their pure melee in a pvp encounter, their effectiveness comes from those annoying abilities everyone loves to hate. That beings said, I don't think bards need any nerf at this moment.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Beastlord: I see beastlords kind of like paladins, melee class with lots of healing power, and semi decent melee. Beastlords do ok in pvp againist some classes. Pvp will never be totally balanced in class vs class situations, but beastlords have good defense skills thx to their heals, and semi decent offense. Plus a pet who does minor dps and interupts. Beatlords also have access to a burst dps ability which can easily do over 1k, useable every 30 seconds. Beastlord nukes are not totally resisted pvp, and land a good portion of the time on the average person. Beastlord slow even lands now and then, believe it or not. In summary beastlords may not have the best offense, but they have good heals. The only thing beastlords need in pvp is a pet upgrade. The 60% pet damage cap should be removed from pvp to resolve this problem and other problems with pets in pvp. Back in the day it was a good idea, as pets could easily and consistently hit pcs in pvp. Nowdays even at low lvs pets are not good dps. The ever changing gear standard has far outpaced pets ability to do decent dps. From level 10 to 70, pets will be useful for nothing but interupts vs 80% of people. The only exception I can think of is the mage epic pet, which outperforms other pets of its level by far, and can be used effectively throughout the low 50s. Besides the epic pet however pets are generally pretty weak. Rogue pet or warrior pet, it doesn't matter, its easy to just ignore them in pvp. Therefore there is no reason to keep the 60% pet damage cap on, as 80% of the people on zek at any level are geared enough for it to make pets underpowered instead of the overpowered it was designed to fix.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Berzerkers: Berzerkers are fine in pvp atm, maybe a little too good even. With 4-5 useful pvp discs and a reliable stun/snare to stop kiters, plus the fact that they innately do high dps, berzerkers need no pvp upgrades atm. An fight between a berzerker and another class with equal gear/aa can easily go ethier way, almost regardless of the class fighting the berzerker. Even a paladin has a chance of being disced on and getting their heals out dpsed by a large % thanks to permastun granted by cleaving anger disc+mind strike. Berzerkers definately need no upgrades.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Cleric: Don't think clerics need any upgrades besides giving their chromatic nuke a better pvp check. They derserve at least one offense spell that lands.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Druid: A druid with barkspur and reptile skin can do pretty decent in pvp vs melees. And druid dots still land effectively, as do their nukes. That being said druids don't really need anything, a druid has both the potental to dps and stay alive if they are played well.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Enchanter: Enchanters have access to very good pells, manadrains, and mezzes. Enchanters just need a better pvp resist check to their pvp nuke so they can go offense if they want to. Of course the chromatic nuke no doubt already lands well on many people, but with coa+geared melees it can be difficult. Not much to ask I don't think, just allow them to get a little damage in instead of mostly resists.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Magician:Mage bolts still land a good amount of the time, regardless of fire resist. Beings an int caster they can take high amounts of damage from melees, but mages never were meant to have good defense. They do have a few spells to help defense, such as pyrilen skin and melee migitation aa. Mages need no upgrades besides their pets which I covered earlier.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Monk: Um, no upgrades needed! With the potential to heal themselves 60% hp every 6min, coupled with another 20% heal every 3, on top of 3.5k heal pot every 2, monks need no upgrades. They do both&amp;nbsp;good dps and have good defense.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Necromancer: Necros need pet upgrade+dot upgrades. Currently necros can only land splurt, pyrocuror, and lifetap in pvp. And even lifetap can be resisted up to 5 times in a row on certain people. Necros need at least a small chance to land their normal dots instead of having to rely on low lv ones. I believe necros are fine for pvp up until 65 or so, only changes to higher lv spells pvp resists need to be made to help their dps.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Paladin: Paladins have a self heal proc ward with a 400 proc rate mod, large mana pools to cast hots and other heals, tons of ac and hp, and access to a 2hander that crits for 1.6k with 700 hits being normal. Paladins may not be able to stop opponents from running, but they are nearly unbeatable in terms of actual fighting. Paladins just need one stun which has a chance to land in pvp. Not a stun that always lands like telakara or zerker stun, just something thats not 92% fail like all their stuns are currently.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Ranger: Rangers have both offense and defense. Naturally a dps class, rangers can dps in pvp easily, and with a horse can stay on anyone and continue to dps as they run.&amp;nbsp;Add their 1.6k heals and 3k crit heals rangers have no problem staying alive in pvp for long periods of time. Plus rangers have access to a chromatic snare which lands frequently on many people, they need no upgrades.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Rogue: Some people may think all rogues are gimpy in pvp, but they'd be wrong. Rogues do about as much pure melee as a monk, just with no heals. The upside is that rogues can backstab for enormous amounts of damage. Recently I took a set of 2 3k backstabs from a rogue during group pvp and died, which is very good backstab damage. A rogue who is skilled and knows how to get behind you can be very good at pvp, and rogues are guaranteed as effective dpsers in group pvp, which is most of the game. I don't see why rogues would need any upgrades at this time, they fufill their role well.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Shadowknight: Shadowknight taps may not land 100%, but they still land enough to heal the sk. Sks are impressive in pvp for the most part, wielding high damage 2handers and able to knock off thousands of hp over time with dots and taps, they also get the benefit of being a tank class, with lots of ac and hp. SKs can hold their own in most situations even without the infamous DT, so I conclude they do not need any upgrades at this time.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Shaman: Shamans's need some of their dots upgraded for sure. The only dot which lands from shamans in pvp is nectar of pain, and even thats not reliable for them. Its certain that a shaman with both many dots that landed pvp and good healing power would be able to pvp effectively. Shaman dots should be changed at higher lvs just like necros, they need a better pvp resist check. Shamans deserve at least 1-2 spells they can count on for when they want to go offense, as currently their best dps is any ds they cast on themselves,and their proc spell.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Wizard: Wizards are ranged dps, glasscannons. With 1.5/2.0 click they can land ether flame and white fire easily, and even without those 2 spell lines land a portion of the time for up to 4k a hit. Plus wizard lures land consistently most of the time. Wizards need no pvp upgrades atm, as they can land spells enough to do decent dps, which is their job.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Warrior: Some people might think warriors are gimp, but they really aren't. As the best tank class and the most hp of any class in the game, as well as the best ac, warriors lower dps is helped by their hp. A long time ago warriors were pretty bad, they would get snared and be unable to do any damage at all, while they slowly died to dots and nukes. Nowdays as resists are getting higher all the time, warriors can resist quite a few spells. That factor along with their flurry aa, warriors can dps well in pvp, easily getting rounds over 1k consistently. Plus warriors now have access to several useful pvp discs, so they don't need to much of an upgrade in todays pvp.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Alright well I know this was a long post, but I wanted to get every class. Hopefully we can all agree on at least a few things here so we can show soe what the community wants.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
