      <title>End of the Line</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=12771#M12771</link>
      <description>&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Well, we tried.&amp;nbsp; Over the last few months we revived our old toons, moved them to Zek, leveled them all to 70, and took a shot at recapturing the magic of EQ for us.&amp;nbsp; For us, anyway, no dice.&amp;nbsp; It's gone, and it's not coming back.&amp;nbsp; We even tried the progression server, but Freeport circa 1999 isn't coming back either.&amp;nbsp; 300 people who know what they're doing trying to race each other to the end-game doesn't feel anything like it did when it was a bunch of people with no idea what they were doing, and every new discovery was golden.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I think the final straw for us is looking at this new expansion.&amp;nbsp; I've tried for months, and I watched others try on this forum, to get SOE to address a PvP system that's fundamentally broken.&amp;nbsp; They don't even bother to pay lip-service anymore.&amp;nbsp; It's all about the next expansion, and the next uber-boss, and the next raid-zone.&amp;nbsp; That's who the game is for now, and that's not us.&amp;nbsp; For those who are out there chewing through each expansion that they pop out, my sincere hope that you have fun with the time that EQ has left.&amp;nbsp; For us, it's time to go.&amp;nbsp; Fortunately we've found a new love in the process of being born.&amp;nbsp; It's a rush to start over again with a new game, and a new world in beta.&amp;nbsp; It's looking good, and our hopes are high.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I wish you all well.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
